le. But this is more about source and API adaptation rather than actual setup requirements. I need to ensure that the JSON is structured as a single object and that there's no extra text or markdown.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No concrete extra Maven dependency, Docker image, environment variable, or system property is required before meaningful coverage is reachable. The artifact already declares its runtime dependencies, and the javac failure is caused by 4.0.0 API/package changes rather than missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Version 4.0.0 exposes the provider through org.neo4j.bolt.connection.netty.NettyBoltConnectionProviderFactory and service loading; earlier 3.0.0 test imports such as org.neo4j.bolt.connection.netty.BootstrapFactory and NettyBoltConnectionProvider no longer compile because implementation classes moved under impl and only the factory package is exported as the intended API.\",\n    \"Meaningful network coverage still requires test code to exercise a Bolt connection, but this can be done with an in-process fake Bolt socket server as in the existing 3.0.0 test; a Neo4j Docker container is not concretely required.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c710b5cfc06707b016a3f0c8d86088195aba2f06e3c9a5272\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 915, "output": 723, "cacheRead": 36864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38502, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782516866236, "responseId": "resp_0c710b5cfc06707b016a3f0c82ba088195a43d19ddb6afb92a"}}
